law.text:
The following actions of the cabinet shall be considered final determinations under KRS 224.1-510 to 224.1-532 that may be appealed in accordance with KRS 224.10-420(2):
Denial of an application to participate in the voluntary environmental remediation program;
Cabinet withdrawal from negotiations with an applicant for an agreed order;
Denial or approval of a corrective action plan; and
Issuance or denial of a covenant not to sue.
